Installation step for angular
1.open CMD first and Close other application if any open (e.g vscode, notepad etc)
-Node js
-angular
-vscode

1.node -v or node --version
2.npm -v or npm --version


To install angular 
npm install -g @angular/cli@7.3.*

3. ng --version

********************************************
if any error occur then use as below Command
npm cache clear --force
npm cache verify
********************************************

Directory
Folder Structure
Frontend
		-TypeScript
		-Angular 
1.open angular folder and after that open cmd

ng new hello-world
Note-(Here hello- world is project name) 
after hitting above command you will get below questions
Which you like to add angular routing? Yes or y 
and do hit enter key

Which stylesheet format would you like? 
do hit enerer key


2.after that do cd hello-world
3.and run the project
to run the project you need to hit this command
ng serve -o 
or
ng serve --open

after successful Creation its open browser automatically ---> http://localhost:4200/






***if angular is already installed and want to take latest version
npm uninstall -g angular-cli
npm cache clean or npm cache verify #(if npm > 5)
npm install -g @angular/cli@7.3.*
















